The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 16: HCL Technologies has signed an agreement to acquire the UK-based BPO provider Liberata Financial Services for an undisclosed amount. As part of the deal, HCL would acquire four delivery centers in the UK with 800 professionals, who come to HCL with domain knowledge and technical expertise, the company said in a statement issued today.                            
	 New Delhi, July 16: Concerned over leakage of sensitive data on price rise, the government has decided to release the inflation figures on Thursdays against the current practice of announcing it on Fridays.                            
	 Islamabad, July 16: Iran, Pakistan and India are expected to hold a meeting in Tehran later this month to push the $7.4-billion gas pipeline project that has been delayed after being caught in a wrangle over transit fee.                             
	 New Delhi, July 16: Telecom regulator Trai has sought details on the department of telecoms proposal of one-time charge for additional spectrum beyond 6.2 Mhz saying it has to be considered from the legal and financial point of view.                            
	 New Delhi, July 16: The Indian Oil Corporation (IOC) is losing Rs 413 crore per day on fuel sales, despite the hike in petrol, diesel and domestic LPG prices.                                                                                                                         
